es in an examination of one of the nation’s first desegregation cases filed jointly by Mexican American and Black plaintiffs. This transdisciplinary history advances our understanding of racism and community resistance across time and place.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aAfrican AmericansxEducationzCaliforniazOxnardxHistoryy20th century. 0aAfrican AmericansxPolitical activityzCaliforniazOxnardy20th century. 0aMexican AmericansxEducationzCaliforniazOxnardxHistoryy20th century. 0aMexicansxPolitical activityzCaliforniazOxnardy20th century. 0aOxnard School District (Calif)bBoard of TrusteesxTrials, litigation, etc. 0aRacism in educationzCaliforniazOxnardy20th century. 0aRacism in educationzCaliforniazOxnard. 0aRacismzCaliforniazOxnardy20th century. 0aRacismzCaliforniazOxnard. 0aSchool integrationzCaliforniazOxnardxHistoryy20th century. 0aSegregation in educationzCaliforniazOxnardy20th century. 0aSegregation in educationzCaliforniazOxnard. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh  a1903 to 1947.  aafrican americans.  aarchival sources.  acalifornia.  acommunity resistance.  adisparate treatment.  afirst desegregation cases.  amexican american and black plaintiffs.  amexican americans.  aoxnard.  aprotested discrimination.  aracial inequality.  aracially restrictive housing covenants.  aracism.  atransdiciplinary history.  aunequal school system.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106676770 cprintz978052029686240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520969179423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520969179/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP